# Debug Statement Guidelines

## Console.log Statements
- Always keep console.log statements to single lines when possible
- Avoid multi-line objects or complex structures in console.log
- Do NOT use emojis or icons in debug statements
- Use clear, descriptive text instead of symbols
- Example: `console.log("Status: " + status + " (" + count + ")")`
- Avoid: `console.log("âœ… Status:", { status, count })`

## Code Style
- Prefer string concatenation over template literals for simple debug messages
- Keep debug messages concise but informative
- Use consistent formatting across all JavaScript files

## When to Use Multi-line
- Only use multi-line console.log when absolutely necessary for complex debugging
- Prefer breaking complex debug info into multiple single-line statements
